snippet: Prime Minister Ali Zeidan said the abduction had been orchestrated by opponents in the legislature who want to force him from office.
abstract: Libyan Prime Min Ali Zeidan says his kidnapping by militia members was no different than a 'coup' and had been orchestrated by opponents in legislature who want to force him from office.

byline.original: By CARLOTTA GALL and MARLISE SIMONS
byline.contributor: Carlotta Gall reported from Tunis, and Marlise Simons from Paris.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Ali Zeidan said the abduction had been orchestrated by opponents in the legislature who want to force him from office.

headline.main: In Libya, Premier Calls Kidnapping Failed ‘Coup’
